40|$|The {{concept of}} {{pervasive}} {{health care system}} was not very old {{but there is still}} a little bit ubiquity between the evaluations of this concept, mean when and from where this concept was developed or evolved. But, the concept of pervasive health care system was developed in late 90 's on the background of some growing medical crisis of baby bom after the Second World War in many industrial countries [Morris et al. ]. Due to the increase of the life-span among the adults, they need the proper treatment from the enormous health care providers. Still many of the diseases that severely limit place an enormous difficult to manage in their later stages like cancer, diabetics, asthma and heart problems, but can be treated more effectively and less expensively if caught in early stages. After World War II, advancement in medical technology began to have an effect on hospital operations. And due to World War II atomic reaction increase in new type of diseases which are not curable at that time [Morris et al. ]. " the early 1990 's, hospitals undergoing another series of changes. This era, in its early stages, appears to be time of consolidation and competition. Within the next 15 to 20 years, a for - profit system composed of hospitals, primary care physicians, specialists, and prepayment plans has been anticipated" [Menon, 2000]. This is a time when most of the hospitals have involved IT and the physicians also involve with IT as well. So after late 1990 's "personal computers were increasingly used by individual departments for specific purposes such as inventory control in pharmacy. Automating clinical records is a relatively a new objective for hospitals. Only in recent years have hospitals attempted to develop <b>integrated</b> <b>cost</b> <b>accounting</b> systems. This dynamic operating environment offers a unique setting in which, to study IT productivity" [Menon, 2000]. Faculty of Technolog...|$|E
