40|$|The {{integrated}} {{product of}} Activity-Based Costing (ABC) and Economic Value Added (EVA) is the ABC & EVA system, i. e. the <b>integrated</b> <b>cost</b> system. Traditional ABC method gives {{priority to the}} interior activity chain of enterprise to implement the cost analysis, but ignores the capital cost, so the <b>cost</b> <b>accounting</b> is not complete. The ABC & EVA system brings the capital cost into the cost management, which could not only open out the real economic value created by the cost objects, but extend the pure cost computation of ABC to the performance evaluation. Based {{on the principle of}} the ABC & EVA system, the enterprise cost control strategies under the <b>integrated</b> <b>cost</b> system are proposed. </p...|$|R
