50|$|In 1970, Congress {{established}} the original <b>Cost</b> <b>Accounting</b> Standards Board (CASB) to 1) promulgate <b>cost</b> <b>accounting</b> standards designed to achieve uniformity and {{consistency in the}} <b>cost</b> <b>accounting</b> principles followed by defense contractors and subcontractors in excess of $100,000 and 2) establish regulations to require defense contractors and subcontractors, {{as a condition of}} contracting, to disclose in writing their <b>cost</b> <b>accounting</b> practices, to follow the disclosed practices consistently and to comply with promulgated <b>cost</b> <b>accounting</b> standards. After adopting 19 standards, the original CASB was dissolved on September 30, 1980; the standards, though, remained active.|$|R
